value.0: This arctic breed of tiger is striped white with dark grey stripes, and has a more subtle coloration than the savannah variety. It also has a more primal, primitive look to it, as if it were the sort of beast a caveman might find, rather than a regal big cat on the prowl. Its fangs are elongated both on the top and the bottom, and it looses a powerful roar before loping towards you and opening its jaw to clamp it down around your neck.
Frozen Wastes: Manticore of Ice Hide
A quiet and deadly hunter seeking prey in the forest.

Hunting in small packs, the Mountain Lions are deadly opponents, especially if they manage to surround you. These animals dwell in the highlands, and are one of the island's less common creatures. The commoners of Forrstakkr have never experienced any troubles with these animals for that reason. Sometimes hunters are sent out to get some of their highly priced and valued fur, and many never come back. A pelt made out of a  Mountain Lion's fur is said to bring fortune to the one who wears it in battle.

"Sneaky kitties... slightly bigger than usual, by the way."  Ionir Aureli, pelthunter.
These stealthy cats avoid humans and hunt at night, so they are rarely seen..
